===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|ls=psc|з•ҫ|зіё|c1=p|c2=s|t2=fine silk}}. The original meaning is "rope; to bind", hence any reference to being tired after hard work in the fields or after sewing is a folk etymology based on modern meaning.

===Etymology===
; вҖңto bind; ropeвҖқ
: From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*rej ~ s-rwi(j)||obscure internal channel; cord; string; creeper; cane; rattan}}; cognate with {{cog|lus|hrui||creeper; cane; rope}}, {{cog|my|бҖӣбҖӯбҖҜбҖё||kind of creeper; tree (''in compounds'')}}.
: Related to {{och-l|иҷҶ|creeper; rambler}}, {{och-l|и—ҹ|to wind; creeper}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}).
: {{cog|tai-pro|*roЛҗjкҹІ||to string together}} (whence {{cog|th|аёЈа№үаёӯаёў}}) may be a loan from Chinese ({{zh-ref|Manomaivibool, 1975}}).

